11UVW_INLINE void FileReq::fsOpenCallback(uv_fs_t *req) {
12 auto ptr = reserve(req);
13
14 if(req->result < 0) {
15 ptr->publish(ErrorEvent{req->result});
16 } else {
17 ptr->file = static_cast<uv_file>(req->result);
18 ptr->publish(FsEvent<Type::OPEN>{req->path});
19 }
20}
21
22
23UVW_INLINE void FileReq::fsCloseCallback(uv_fs_t *req) {
24 auto ptr = reserve(req);
25
26 if(req->result < 0) {
27 ptr->publish(ErrorEvent{req->result});
28 } else {
29 ptr->file = BAD_FD;
30 ptr->publish(FsEvent<Type::CLOSE>{req->path});
31 }
32}
33
34
35UVW_INLINE void FileReq::fsReadCallback(uv_fs_t *req) {
36 auto ptr = reserve(req);
37
38 if(req->result < 0) {
39 ptr->publish(ErrorEvent{req->result});
40 } else {
41 ptr->publish(FsEvent<Type::READ>{req->path, std::move(ptr->current), static_cast<std::size_t>(req->result)});
42 }
43}

51UVW_INLINE void FileReq::close() {
52 cleanupAndInvoke(&uv_fs_close, parent(), get(), file, &fsCloseCallback);
53}

55
56UVW_INLINE bool FileReq::closeSync() {
57 auto req = get();
58
59 cleanupAndInvokeSync(&uv_fs_close, parent(), req, file);
60
61 if(req->result >= 0) {
62 file = BAD_FD;
63 }
64
65 return !(req->result < 0);
66}

74UVW_INLINE bool FileReq::openSync(std::string path, Flags<FileOpen> flags, int mode) {
75 auto req = get();
76
77 cleanupAndInvokeSync(&uv_fs_open, parent(), req, path.data(), flags, mode);
78
79 if(req->result >= 0) {
80 file = static_cast<uv_file>(req->result);
81 }
82
83 return !(req->result < 0);
84}

87UVW_INLINE void FileReq::read(int64_t offset, unsigned int len) {
88 current = std::unique_ptr<char[]>{new char[len]};
89 buffer = uv_buf_init(current.get(), len);
90 uv_buf_t bufs[] = {buffer};
91 cleanupAndInvoke(&uv_fs_read, parent(), get(), file, bufs, 1, offset, &fsReadCallback);
92}

94
95UVW_INLINE std::pair<bool, std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const char[]>, std::size_t>> FileReq::readSync(int64_t offset, unsigned int len) {
96 current = std::unique_ptr<char[]>{new char[len]};
97 buffer = uv_buf_init(current.get(), len);
98 uv_buf_t bufs[] = {buffer};
99 auto req = get();
100 cleanupAndInvokeSync(&uv_fs_read, parent(), req, file, bufs, 1, offset);
101 bool err = req->result < 0;
102 return std::make_pair(!err, std::make_pair(std::move(current), err ? 0 : std::size_t(req->result)));
103}

231UVW_INLINE void FsReq::fsReadlinkCallback(uv_fs_t *req) {
232 auto ptr = reserve(req);
233
234 if(req->result < 0) {
235 ptr->publish(ErrorEvent{req->result});
236 } else {
237 ptr->publish(FsEvent<Type::READLINK>{req->path, static_cast<char *>(req->ptr), static_cast<std::size_t>(req->result)});
238 }
239}
240
241
242UVW_INLINE void FsReq::fsReaddirCallback(uv_fs_t *req) {
243 auto ptr = reserve(req);
244
245 if(req->result < 0) {
246 ptr->publish(ErrorEvent{req->result});
247 } else {
248 auto *dir = static_cast<uv_dir_t *>(req->ptr);
249 ptr->publish(FsEvent<Type::READDIR>{dir->dirents[0].name, static_cast<EntryType>(dir->dirents[0].type), !req->result});
250 }
251}

299
300UVW_INLINE std::pair<bool, std::pair<std::string, std::size_t>> FsReq::mkstempSync(std::string tpl) {
301 std::pair<bool, std::pair<std::string, std::size_t>> ret{false, {}};
302 auto req = get();
303 cleanupAndInvokeSync(&uv_fs_mkdtemp, parent(), req, tpl.data());
304 ret.first = !(req->result < 0);
305
306 if(ret.first) {
307 ret.second.first = req->path;
308 ret.second.second = static_cast<std::size_t>(req->result);
309 }
310
311 return ret;
312}

351
352UVW_INLINE std::pair<bool, std::pair<FsReq::EntryType, const char *>> FsReq::scandirNext() {
353 std::pair<bool, std::pair<EntryType, const char *>> ret{false, { EntryType::UNKNOWN, nullptr }};
354
355 // we cannot use cleanupAndInvokeSync because of the return value of uv_fs_scandir_next
356 uv_fs_req_cleanup(get());
357 auto res = uv_fs_scandir_next(get(), dirents);
358
359 if(UV_EOF != res) {
360 ret.second.first = static_cast<EntryType>(dirents[0].type);
361 ret.second.second = dirents[0].name;
362 ret.first = true;
363 }
364
365 return ret;
366}

574UVW_INLINE std::pair<bool, std::pair<FsReq::EntryType, const char *>> FsReq::readdirSync() {
575 auto req = get();
576 auto *dir = static_cast<uv_dir_t *>(req->ptr);
577 dir->dirents = dirents;
578 dir->nentries = 1;
579 cleanupAndInvokeSync(&uv_fs_readdir, parent(), req, dir);
580 return {req->result != 0, { static_cast<EntryType>(dirents[0].type), dirents[0].name }};
581}
